<span class="displaytext"><b>to: interested parties<br/> from: (candidate last) campaign<br/> date: monday, march 03, 2008<br/> regarding: questions sen. (candidate last) should answer about tony rezko </b> <p><i>the trial of indicted influence peddler tony rezko - longtime friend and political patron of sen. (candidate full) -- starts today . sen. (candidate last)'s name has already surfaced in pre-trial documents submitted by the prosecution and, according to media reports, is likely to surface again as the trial progresses. (PARTY NAME) deserve the answers to these questions as they consider their votes:</i> </p><p><b>1. will sen. (candidate last) release all documents related to his relationship with tony rezko, including all documents related to his controversial land transaction?</b> </p><p>howard wolfson asked top (candidate last) strategist david axelrod this question on abc's this week and the campaign has yet to respond. [abc's this week, 3/2/08] </p><p><b>2. when, specifically, did sen. (candidate last) become aware of mr. rezko's legal problems?</b> </p><p>on national television this january, sen. (candidate last) said "no one had an inkling" of rezko's legal troubles during the course of their relationship. actually, it was already widely reported that mr. rezko was under investigation for participating in a kickback scheme prior to their controversial land transaction. [cbs, 1/23/08; chicago sun-times, 9/16/05] </p><p><b>3. sen. (candidate last) has returned money from several individuals who are publicly associated with mr. rezko. how much money did mr. rezko bundle for sen. (candidate last)'s campaigns in total, including people who are not business associates of mr. rezko? how many fundraisers did mr. rezko hold for sen. (candidate last)? has there been an internal investigation to determine how many straw donors mr. rezko used to funnel money to sen. (candidate last)? </b></p><p>the (candidate last) campaign has returned money from people who are publicly associate with mr. rezko. but they have not revealed who much mr. rezko bundled for sen. (candidate last) in total. the chicago sun times reported that the (candidate last) campaign "declined to say" whether they maintained a list of the money that mr. rezko raised for mr. (candidate last) over the course of his career. [chicago sun times, 1/23/08] </p><p><b>4. much of the upcoming trial involves mr. rezko's efforts to control state boards as a means to defraud the state government. have sen. (candidate last) and mr. rezko ever communicated about potential appointments to illinois boards and commissions? it's been publicly reported that sen. (candidate last) lobbied these same state boards to secure contracts for campaign donors. did sen. (candidate last) ever confer with mr. rezko concerning how to successfully lobby state boards?</b> </p><p>the indictment alleges that mr. rezko manipulated state government boards to defraud the people of illinois. at the same time, "mr. (candidate last) met with three state pension boards," urging them to give contracts to specific firms. later, employees of these companies "donated more than $300,000 to help mr. (candidate last) win his seat in the united states senate in 2004 and set fund-raising records early in the 2008 presidential race." [new york times, 10/01/07] </p><p><b>5. the new york times reported that sen. (candidate last) attended a business meeting on behalf of mr. rezko to impress potential investors for his business schemes. how many events did sen. (candidate last) attend on behalf of mr. rezko to impress investors? what was his role? why did sen. (candidate last) agree to attend?</b> </p><p>the new york times reported in june that "former rezko associates said that governor blagojevich attended one of the dinners, and that at mr. rezko's request, mr. (candidate last) dropped in at one for middle eastern bankers in early 2004, just as he was starting to pull ahead in the senate primary. the visits, mr. rezko's partners said, helped impress foreign guests." [new york times, 6/14/07] </p><p><b>6. how many times did senator (candidate last) visit tony rezko's house? what was the purpose of these visits?</b> </p><p>the times of london reports that "the court is also expected to hear from john thomas, an fbi mole, who reportedly witnessed mr (candidate last) and mr blagojevich making frequent visits to mr rezko." [the times, 3/3/08] </p><p><b>7. did sen. (candidate last) intercede on behalf of mr. rezko in any governmental capacity?</b> </p><p>the chicago sun times reported that "as a state senator, (candidate full) wrote letters to city and state officials supporting his political patron tony rezko's successful bid to get more than $14 million from taxpayers to build apartments for senior citizens." they have not said whether there were any other actions that (candidate last) took for the benefit of rezko. [chicago sun times, 6/13/07]</p></span>



